n29: - [ ] **2.5** Define `AgentRuntimeListResponse` struct in `types.go`\n30: - [ ] **2.6** Define `CodeInterpreterListResponse` struct in `types.go`\n31: - [ ] **2.7** Define `CreateAgentRuntimeRequest` struct in `types.go`\n32: - [ ] **2.8** Define `CreateCodeInterpreterRequest` struct in `types.go`\n33: - [ ] **2.9** Define `UpdateAgentRuntimeRequest` struct in `types.go`\n34: - [ ] **2.10** Define `UpdateCodeInterpreterRequest` struct in `types.go`\n35: - [ ] **2.11** Define `Config` struct in `server.go` - server configuration with port, graceful shutdown timeout\n36: - [ ] **2.12** Define `Server` struct in `server.go` - HTTP server wrapper\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ## Phase 3: Service Interface Implementation\n41: \n42: - [ ] **3.1** Define `WorkloadManager` interface in `service.go`\n43: - [ ] **3.2** Implement `workloadManagerImpl` struct in `service.go`\n44: - [ ] **3.3** Implement `NewWorkloadManager` constructor function\n45: - [ ] **3.4** Implement `CreateAgentRuntime` method\n46: - [ ] **3.5** Implement `GetAgentRuntime` method\n47: - [ ] **3.6** Implement `ListAgentRuntimes` method with labelSelector support\n48: - [ ] **3.7** Implement `UpdateAgentRuntime` method\n49: - [ ] **3.8** Implement `DeleteAgentRuntime` method\n50: - [ ] **3.9** Implement `GetAgentRuntimeStatus` method\n51: - [ ] **3.10** Implement `PatchAgentRuntimeStatus` method\n52: - [ ] **3.11** Implement `WatchAgentRuntimes` method (for watch=true queries)\n53: - [ ] **3.12** Implement `CreateCodeInterpreter` method\n54: - [ ] **3.13** Implement `GetCodeInterpreter` method\n55: - [ ] **3.14** Implement `ListCodeInterpreters` method with labelSelector support\n56: - [ ] **3.15** Implement `UpdateCodeInterpreter` method\n57: - [ ] **3.16** Implement `DeleteCodeInterpreter` method\n58: - [ ] **3.17** Implement `GetCodeInterpreterStatus` method\n59: - [ ] **3.18** Implement `PatchCodeInterpreterStatus` method\n60: - [ ] **3.19** Implement `WatchCodeInterpreters` method\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## Phase 4: Kubernetes Client Integration\n65: \n66: - [ ] **4.1** Implement `NewK8sClient` function in `client.go` - create Kubernetes clientset from kubeconfig\n67: - [ ] **4.2** Implement `NewInClusterClient` function in `client.go` - create client for in-cluster mode\n68: - [ ] **4.3** Implement `NewClientset` function in `client.go` - create typed clientset for AgentCube CRDs\n69: - [ ] **4.4** Implement `NewInformerFactory` function in `client.go` - create SharedInformerFactory\n70: - [ ] **4.5** Implement `RegisterInformers` method in `server.go` - register AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter informers\n71: - [ ] **4.6** Implement `StartInformers` method in `server.go` - start informers and wait for cache sync\n72: - [ ] **4.7** Implement client cleanup in `Close` method - close HTTP clients without goroutine leaks\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## Phase 5: HTTP Handlers\n77: \n78: - [ ] **5.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/agentruntime.go`\n79: - [ ] **5.2** Implement `HandleCreateAgentRuntime` handler - POST /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes\n80: - [ ] **5.3** Implement `HandleGetAgentRuntime` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}\n81: - [ ] **5.4** Implement `HandleListAgentRuntimes` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes (with labelSelector, watch)\n82: - [ ] **5.5** Implement `HandleUpdateAgentRuntime` handler - PUT /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}\n83: - [ ] **5.6** Implement `HandleDeleteAgentRuntime` handler - DELETE /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}\n84: - [ ] **5.7** Implement `HandleGetAgentRuntimeStatus` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}/status\n85: - [ ] **5.8** Implement `HandlePatchAgentRuntimeStatus` handler - PATCH /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}/status\n86: - [ ] **5.9** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/codeinterpreter.go`\n87: - [ ] **5.10** Implement `HandleCreateCodeInterpreter` handler - POST /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters\n88: - [ ] **5.11** Implement `HandleGetCodeInterpreter` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters/{name}\n89: - [ ] **5.12** Implement `HandleListCodeInterpreters` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters\n90: - [ ] **5.13** Implement `HandleUpdateCodeInterpreter` handler - PUT /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters/{name}\n91: - [ ] **5.14** Implement `HandleDeleteCodeInterpreter` handler - DELETE /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters/{name}\n92: - [ ] **5.15** Implement `HandleGetCodeInterpreterStatus` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status\n93: - [ ] **5.16** Implement `HandlePatchCodeInterpreterStatus` handler - PATCH /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status\n94: - [ ] **5.17** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go`\n95: - [ ] **5.18** Implement `HandleHealthz` handler - GET /healthz (liveness probe, returns \"ok\")\n96: - [ ] **5.19** Implement `HandleReadyz` handler - GET /readyz (readiness probe, 200 when ready, 503 when not)\n97: - [ ] **5.20** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/metrics.go`\n98: - [ ] **5.21** Implement `HandleMetrics` handler - Prometheus metrics endpoint\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## Phase 6: Middleware Implementation\n103: \n104: - [ ] **6.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go`\n105: - [ ] **6.2** Implement `LoggingMiddleware` function - logs method, path, status code, latency\n106: - [ ] **6.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/error.go`\n107: - [ ] **6.4** Define error codes constants in `error.go` (ErrCodeInvalidRequest, ErrCodeNotFound, etc.)\n108: - [ ] **6.5** Implement `ErrorMiddleware` function - map Kubernetes API errors to HTTP status codes\n109: - [ ] **6.6** Implement `handleAPIError` function - structured error response with message, reason, code\n110: - [ ] **6.7** Implement `httpStatusForErrorCode` function - error code to HTTP status mapping\n111: - [ ] **6.8** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go`\n112: - [ ] **6.9** Implement `CORSMiddleware` function - handle CORS preflight requests\n113: - [ ] **6.10** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery.go`\n114: - [ ] **6.11** Implement `RecoveryMiddleware` function - recover from panics, return 500\n115: \n116: ---\n117: \n118: ## Phase 7: Server Setup & Graceful Shutdown\n119: \n120: - [ ] **7.1** Implement `NewServer` constructor function in `server.go`\n121: - [ ] **7.2** Implement `setupRouter` method in `server.go` - configure Gin router\n122: - [ ] **7.3** Configure middleware stack (Logging, Recovery, CORS, Error)\n123: - [ ] **7.4** Implement `RegisterRoutes` method - wire up all route groups\n124: - [ ] **7.5** Implement `Start` method - start HTTP server with configurable port\n125: - [ ] **7.6** Implement graceful shutdown logic - stop accepting new requests, finish existing ones\n126: - [ ] **7.7** Handle SIGTERM/SIGINT signals for shutdown trigger\n127: - [ ] **7.8** Implement shutdown timeout handling (default 30 seconds)\n128: - [ ] **7.9** Shutdown informers on server stop\n129: \n130: ---\n131: \n132: ## Phase 8: Configuration & CLI Entry Point\n133: \n134: - [ ] **8.1** Create `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n135: - [ ] **8.2** Implement command-line flag parsing (--port, --kubeconfig, etc.)\n136: - [ ] **8.3** Default port: 8080\n137: - [ ] **8.4** Implement environment variable loading\n138: - [ ] **8.5** Wire up configuration from flags/env to `Config` struct\n139: - [ ] **8.6** Initialize Kubernetes client (from kubeconfig or in-cluster)\n140: - [ ] **8.7** Initialize WorkloadManager service\n141: - [ ] **8.8** Initialize and start server\n142: - [ ] **8.9** Handle startup errors and exit gracefully\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ## Phase 9: Unit Tests\n147: \n148: - [ ] **9.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/mocks_test.go` - mock implementations for testing\n149: - [ ] **9.2** Implement `MockWorkloadManager` struct with function fields\n150: - [ ] **9.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/ag